land, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1238–1334":"about 1238–1334","1238–1334":"1238–1334","1245–1290":"1245–1290","1272–1358":"1272–1358","1175–Male":"1175–Deceased","1315":"1315","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1358":"1358","1334":"1334","1245":"1245","Abt 1238":"about 1238","1175":"1175","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Drinkstone, Suffolk, England":"Drinkstone, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Shouldham, Norfolk, England":"Shouldham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Burgate","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name, nickname denoting someone who lived ‘(by the) town gate’, or who was the keeper of the Bargate."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":21,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":52,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":77,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":90,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Burgate was born about 1238, in Suffolk, England as the daughter of Roger Burgate. She married Robert Bacon in 1272, in Hessett, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1334, in Hessett, Suffolk, England, at the age of 97, and was buried in Hessett, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1238–1334":"umbes 1238–1334","1238–1334":"1238–1334","1245–1290":"1245–1290","1272–1358":"1272–1358","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1315":"1315","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1358":"1358","1334":"1334","1245":"1245","Abt 1238":"umbes 1238","1175":"1175","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Drinkstone, Suffolk, England":"Drinkstone, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Shouldham, Norfolk, England":"Shouldham, Norfolk, I